# Northbound Treatment — Design System

Use this as the single source of truth when building any page, section, or component inside `apps/northbound-treatment`.

---

## Brand Palette

All tokens are defined in `src/app/globals.css` via `@theme inline` and available as Tailwind utilities (`bg-navy`, `text-terracotta`, etc.).

| Token | Hex | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `navy` | `#1b2a47` | Primary dark, headings on light, dark section backgrounds, buttons |
| `navy-light` | `#2a3d66` | Button hover, secondary navy tint |
| `terracotta` | `#e97a52` | Primary accent — CTAs, eyebrows, icons, star ratings, links |
| `terracotta-light` | `#f09068` | Hover state for terracotta elements |
| `espresso` | `#2c2a28` | Body text on light backgrounds |
| `sand` | `#eef2f7` | Alternating section background (cool slate-blue, not warm beige) |
| `sand-light` | `#ffffff` | Primary white background |
| `sand-dark` | `#cdd8e8` | Borders and dividers |
| `agave` | `#7a8b76` | Subtle accent (used sparingly) |

**Never use warm beige (`#f4efe6`, `#e5dccb`), old charcoal (`#374151`), or old navy (`#4a6a92`) — these are retired.**

---

## Typography

| Role | Class | Font | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| All headings | `font-heading` | Playfair Display (serif) | Loaded as `--font-playfair` |
| Body / UI | `font-sans` or default | DM Sans | Loaded as `--font-dm-sans` |
| Italic accent word in headings | `<span className="italic text-terracotta">word</span>` | — | Use on light bg |
| Italic accent on dark bg | `<span className="italic text-terracotta-light">word</span>` | — | Use on navy bg |
| Eyebrows | `text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-terracotta` | DM Sans | Always above h2 |

**H1 hero**: `font-heading text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold text-white` (on dark), or `text-navy` (on light)
**H2 sections**: `font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-navy` (light) or `text-white` (dark)
**H3 cards**: `font-heading text-lg md:text-xl font-bold`

---

## Layout Container

```tsx
const CONTAINER = "mx-auto w-full max-w-7xl px-6 lg:px-10";
```

Use on **every** section. Never use `max-w-5xl` or `max-w-6xl` on new pages.

---

## Section Background Rhythm

Alternate between these to create visual cadence throughout a page:

1. **White** (`bg-white` / `bg-sand-light`) — default
2. **Slate** (`bg-sand`) — cool `#eef2f7` tint, alternating sections
3. **Navy** (`bg-navy`) — dark accent sections (CTA strips, modalities, testimonials, insurance)

Dark navy sections always use `text-white` and `text-terracotta` for accents. Never put dark-bg sections back-to-back without a white/slate break.

---

## Borders & Radius

- `--radius-*` tokens are all `0` — **sharp corners everywhere** (no `rounded-full` on structural containers)
- Exception: decorative floating cards, pills, and stat overlays use `rounded-2xl` / `rounded-3xl` / `rounded-full` intentionally
- Dividers: `border-sand-dark` (`#cdd8e8`)
- Architectural lines: use `.architectural-border`, `.architectural-border-top`, `.architectural-border-bottom`, `.architectural-border-l` utility classes

---

## Buttons

**Primary (navy fill):**
```tsx
className="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-navy px-7 py-3.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm transition hover:bg-navy-light"
```

**Primary (terracotta fill):**
```tsx
className="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-terracotta px-7 py-3.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm transition hover:bg-terracotta-light"
```

**Outline on light bg:**
```tsx
className="inline-flex items-center gap-2 border border-terracotta/30 px-7 py-3.5 text-sm font-semibold text-terracotta transition hover:border-terracotta hover:bg-terracotta/5"
```

**Outline on dark bg:**
```tsx
className="inline-flex items-center gap-2 border border-white/30 px-7 py-3.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition hover:border-white/60 hover:bg-white/10"
```

**Text link:**
```tsx
className="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm font-semibold text-terracotta underline-offset-4 hover:underline"
```

